H0.text: Prokaryotic cells are cells without a nucleus.

H1.text: Monocyte cells are cells without a nucleus.

H2.text: Heterogeneous cells are cells without a nucleus.

H3.text: Crustal cells are cells without a nucleus.

A4.text: Prokaryotes are microorganisms whose usually single cell lacks a nucleus or other membrane-bound organelles.

A5.text: The genome in a prokaryote is held within a DNA/protein complex in the cytosol called the nucleoid, which lacks a nuclear envelope.
